`;await e.writeFile("/guidelines/setup.md",'## Step 1: Install css\n\nAdd this line to the TOP of `/src/styles/index.css` (before any other imports):\n\n```css\n@import "<PACKAGE_NAME>/style.css";\n```\n\nThis import defines all CSS custom properties (color tokens, spacing tokens,\nradius tokens) used by this design system. Without it, var(--token-name)\nreferences will resolve to nothing and the UI will have no styling.\n\n## Step 2: Read the full design system stylesheet\n\nAfter importing, read the full contents of the stylesheet to understand what\ntokens are available:\n\n```\ncat node_modules/<PACKAGE_NAME>/dist/style.css\n```\n\nDo NOT use `head -100` or any truncated read. The file begins with Tailwind\npreflight/reset CSS (box-sizing, margins, etc.) which is NOT the design system.\nThe actual token definitions (CSS custom properties like `--text-default`,\n`--bg-brand`, `--spacer-*`, etc.) appear AFTER the preflight section.\n\nScan the full output for `:root` or `@theme` blocks containing `--` custom\nproperty definitions. These are the tokens you must use in generated code.\n'),await e.writeFile(em.dY,r)}var eC=n(415305),eI=n(534693),eE=n(925453),eT=n(434853),eS=n(991570),eN=n(526598),eA=n(793518),eO=n(145786),eR=n(249604);function eD({onNext:e}){return(0,a.useEffect)(()=>{e()},[e]),null}var eM=n(33652);let eF=new Set(["dependencies","devDependencies","peerDependencies"]);function eP(e){try{let t=JSON.parse(e);return"object"==typeof t&&null!==t?t:null}catch{return null}}function eL(e){if(!e)return new Set;let t=[];for(let n of eF){let r=e[n];r&&"object"==typeof r&&t.push(...Object.keys(r))}return new Set(t)}function ez(e){let t={};for(let n of e.listFiles())n.metadata.isHidden||"string"==typeof n.contents&&(t[n.path]=n.contents);return t}function eU(e,t){let n=eP(e["/package.json"]??"{}"),r=eP(t["/package.json"]??"{}"),a=eL(n);return[...eL(r)].filter(e=>!a.has(e))}let eG="{{SETUP_DIFF}}",eB=`Your job is to examine the project setup and produce a setup guideline document that an AI code-generation agent can later use to correctly configure new projects to use this design system.

## Input

${eG}

The npm package list and agent constraints have been pre-written to \`/guidelines/setup.md\`. Read that file to see which packages to analyze.

## IMPORTANT: Output location
Read the existing \`/guidelines/setup.md\` file first, then APPEND your findings below the existing content. Do NOT remove or modify the pre-written sections. Do NOT write any other files. Do NOT print the guidelines to chat \u2014 write them as a file.

## What to document in \`/guidelines/setup.md\`

- **Install instructions**: the exact install instructions with all required packages (peer dependencies included).
- **Required CSS imports**: list every CSS file that must be imported and the recommended import order.
- **Provider / wrapper components**: if the design system requires a provider component at the app root, document it with all required props and show the recommended entry point pattern.
- **Build tool configuration**: any required Vite/Webpack/PostCSS/Tailwind configuration.
- **TypeScript**: any \`tsconfig.json\` requirements.
- **Peer dependencies**: list all peer dependencies and their version constraints.
- **Common gotchas**: things that silently break if misconfigured.

## Process

For each installed package, find and read the most informative files. Prioritize:

1. **README / CHANGELOG** \u2014 setup instructions, provider requirements, and usage examples.
2. **package.json** \u2014 check \`peerDependencies\`, \`exports\` (entry points), and \`style\`/\`css\` fields (required CSS imports).
3. **Type definitions** (\`.d.ts\` files) \u2014 provider components, configuration types.
4. **CSS/SCSS source files** \u2014 required CSS imports, theme files.

Do NOT rely on external documentation websites. Everything you need must come from what is shipped in the packages.

## Formatting rules

- Use Markdown for all output.
- Use fenced code blocks with language tags for all code examples.
- Keep the document concise but complete \u2014 target 100-300 lines.
- Do not invent information. If a token or prop doesn't exist in the installed packages, omit it.
- Order content from most-used to least-used.`;function eK({initialBaselineFiles:e,chatMessagesNodeGuid:t}){let n=eC.v.getFeatureGate("make_kits_npm_context_extraction"),[i,s]=(0,a.useState)("configuring"),o=(0,g.md)((0,eE.Uy)(t)),[l,d]=(0,a.useState)(e);return(0,a.useEffect)(()=>{"generating"===i&&(o===eE.vO.COMMITTED?s("done"):o===eE.vO.ERROR||o===eE.vO.ABORTED?s("error"):o===eE.vO.USER_ABORTED&&s("skipped"))},[i,o]),(0,a.useMemo)(()=>{let e=(0,r.jsx)(eN.E,{variant:"inactiveOutline",size:"md",children:(0,X.t)("figmake.import_progress.section.add_custom_configuration.optional_badge")});return"done"===i?{label:(0,X.t)("figmake.import_progress.section.applied_custom_configuration"),badge:e,showCheckmark:!0,activeContent:e=>(0,r.jsx)(eD,{onNext:e})}:"skipped"===i?{label:(0,X.t)("figmake.import_progress.section.add_custom_configuration"),badge:e,showCheckmark:!1,activeContent:e=>(0,r.jsx)(eD,{onNext:e})}:"error"===i?{label:(0,X.t)("figmake.import_progress.section.add_custom_configuration"),badge:e,activeContent:e=>(0,r.jsx)("div",{...h.xk(ea.l.stepContent),children:(0,r.jsx)(eo.F,{variant:"secondary",onClick:e,children:(0,X.t)("figmake.import_progress.button.next")})})}:"generating"===i?{label:(0,X.t)("figmake.import_progress.section.applying_custom_configuration"),badge:e,showSpinner:!0,activeContent:()=>(0,r.jsx)(eq,{baselineFiles:l,onDone:()=>{s("done")},onError:()=>{s("error")}})}:{label:(0,X.t)("figmake.import_progress.section.add_custom_configuration"),badge:e,activeContent:e=>(0,r.jsxs)("div",{...h.xk(ea.l.stepContent),children:[(0,r.jsx)(eH,{baselineFiles:l,setBaselineFiles:d}),(0,r.jsx)("span",{...h.xk(ea.l.subtext),children:(0,X.tx)("figmake.import_progress.section.add_custom_configuration.subtext",{learnMoreLink:(0,r.jsx)("button",{...h.xk(ea.l.learnMoreLink),type:"button",onClick:eA.lQ,children:(0,X.t)("figmake.import_progress.section.add_custom_configuration.learn_more")})})}),(0,r.jsx)(eo.F,{variant:"secondary",onClick:()=>{n?s("generating"):e()},children